(43, 12, 39, 23, 6, 9, 10, 'could not believe', 'Connection of Unbelief and Understanding', 'This connection highlights the theme of unbelief in both passages. John 12:39 refers to Isaiah''s prophecy about the people''s inability to believe, which is elaborated in Isaiah 6:9-10, where the people''s hearts are made unresponsive to understanding.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 39, 43, 5, 44, 44, 'could not believe', 'Belief and Honor Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the difficulty of belief. In John 12:39, the inability to believe is linked to external influences, while John 5:44 highlights the issue of seeking honor from others instead of God, suggesting that misplaced priorities hinder faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
